{"actor":"ddx","body":"success\nThe fix matches option 1 from the bead: harbor_agent installs ca-certificates inside the container before uploading and running the fiz binary. The implementation is appropriately defensive — it short-circuits when a CA bundle already exists, supports the three major package-manager families, and uses `set +e` / `exit 0` so offline or otherwise locked-down images don't hard-fail the run. Placement before the binary upload ensures the first TLS handshake from fiz has trust roots available.\nresult_rev=38b5d6c6115204213437f1cda681b18ed5a7fc96\nbase_rev=d03d461ddfd1964eb0471ef409610abaa158d543","created_at":"2026-05-03T02:03:08.842122022Z","kind":"execute-bead","source":"ddx agent execute-loop","summary":"success"}
